National Orientation Agency (NOA) on Thursday engaged students in tertiary institutions in Enugu on attitudinal re-orientation to address moral decadence among the youths. The one day summit was held at the Godfrey Okoye University (GOUNI) in Enugu with the theme “Youth Participation in National Development in the face of COVID-19”. The Director General of (NOA) Dr Garba Abari said the summit was to reawaken the consciousness of Nigerian youths, particularly students of tertiary institutions on the menace of social vices in the tertiary institutions and means to end them. 